The paper deals with the problem of testing whether a graph has bounded arboricity, which is a fundamental concept in graph theory and has applications in various areas of computer science. The paper presents a tolerant tester in the sparse-graphs model, which is a well-studied model in computer science. The techniques used in the paper involve local simulation and edge sampling, which are common tools in the field of graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.IT (Information Theory), which are all relevant to the topic of the paper.
